      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "bc6a448b16f9fce72f384eca8ad423e5e4b5e991",
            "subject": "LU-3738 tests: improve posix.sh to support BASELINE_FS=zfs"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "James Nunez",
          "email": "james.a.nunez@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-09-26 21:21:42.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-12-30 22:32:54.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-3764 tests: Make calls to error_ignore not trigger FAIL",
        "message": "LU-3764 tests: Make calls to error_ignore not trigger FAIL\n\nCurrently, error_ignore calls error_noexit with a status of IGNORE\nand a message/comment. error_noexit writes the comment to\nthe $LOGDIR/err file. If there is an err file, the pass\nroutine assumes the test failed and reports the test status as FAIL.\nSo, for errors that should be ignored, we don't want to be\nwriting the comment out to the err file.\n\nNow, any message with an \"IGNORE\" status is written to\n$LOGDIR/ignore file and, thus, the test will no longer be\nclassified as FAIL and the error will really be ignored.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I30f5387105f6cbce54050682b16387f73ab541d6\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/7782\nReviewed-by: Minh Diep <minh.diep@intel.com>\nTested-by: Hudson\nTested-by: Maloo <whamcloud.maloo@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Jian Yu <jian.yu@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
  },
